data: {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_016HK4bQdc1bGsGFy91af36k","content":"Sandbox containers are spawned and managed by the **Centaur API** (v2) using a pluggable sandbox backend system, primarily targeting **Docker**.\n\nThe core logic for creating containers resides in the following files:\n\n### 1. Docker Container Creation\nThe `DockerSandboxBackend` class handles the low-level Docker SDK calls to run agent containers. It configures the environment, bind-mounts necessary directories (like the codebase and firewall certificates), and waits for the container to be ready.\n- [services/api/api/sandbox/docker.py#L150-L243](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/sandbox/docker.py#L150-L243) \u2014 The `create` method that calls `client.containers.run`.\n- [services/api/api/sandbox/docker.py#L49-L84](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/sandbox/docker.py#L49-L84) \u2014 Environment variable provisioning for the sandbox (proxies, API keys).\n\n### 2. Sandbox Orchestration\nThe `agent.py` module acts as the orchestration layer, managing session state in Postgres and deciding whether to claim a \"warm\" container or spawn a new one.\n- [services/api/api/agent.py#L399-L461](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/agent.py#L399-L461) \u2014 `get_or_spawn` logic that coordinates session recovery, warm pool claiming, and cold spawning.\n- [services/api/api/agent.py#L182-L197](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/agent.py#L182-L197) \u2014 `_spawn_sync` helper that invokes the backend's `create` method.\n\n### 3. Warm Pool Management\nTo eliminate startup latency, the API maintains a pool of pre-warmed, idle Docker containers.\n- [services/api/api/warm_pool.py#L62-L96](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/warm_pool.py#L62-L96) \u2014 Logic for spawning anonymous \"warm\" containers.\n- [services/api/api/warm_pool.py#L202-L262](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/warm_pool.py#L202-L262) \u2014 `claim_container` logic which renames and re-tokens a warm container for a specific user thread.\n- [services/api/api/warm_pool.py#L99-L200](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/warm_pool.py#L99-L200) \u2014 `_inject_persona` which uses `docker exec` to provision a warm container with specific persona/repo data after it has been claimed.\n\n### 4. Sandbox Interface\nThe abstract base class defines the interface for any sandbox backend (e.g., Docker, or potentially others like Firecracker/Iron).\n- [services/api/api/sandbox/base.py#L47-L101](file:///home/agent/github/example/centaur/services/api/api/sandbox/base.py#L47-L101) \u2014 The `SandboxBackend` abstract base class.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019ce048-862f-7331-b7ee-fa1eb74547f9"}

data: {"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sandbox containers are spawned in the centaur API service via a layered system: the abstract interface is defined in `services/api/api/sandbox/base.py`, with the concrete Docker implementation in `services/api/api/sandbox/docker.py` (the `create` method at ~L150 calls `client.containers.run` with bind-mounts, env vars, and networking). Orchestration lives in `services/api/api/agent.py` (~L399, `get_or_spawn`), which decides whether to claim a pre-warmed container or cold-spawn a new one. The warm pool system in `services/api/api/warm_pool.py` pre-creates idle Docker containers and, upon claim, injects persona/repo data via `docker exec` to cut startup latency."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":976,"cache_read_input_tokens":24845,"output_tokens":184,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019ce048-862f-7331-b7ee-fa1eb74547f9"}

data: {"type":"turn.done","turn_id":1,"result":"Sandbox containers are spawned in the centaur API service via a layered system: the abstract interface is defined in `services/api/api/sandbox/base.py`, with the concrete Docker implementation in `services/api/api/sandbox/docker.py` (the `create` method at ~L150 calls `client.containers.run` with bind-mounts, env vars, and networking). Orchestration lives in `services/api/api/agent.py` (~L399, `get_or_spawn`), which decides whether to claim a pre-warmed container or cold-spawn a new one. The warm pool system in `services/api/api/warm_pool.py` pre-creates idle Docker containers and, upon claim, injects persona/repo data via `docker exec` to cut startup latency.","agent_thread_id":"T-019ce048-862f-7331-b7ee-fa1eb74547f9"}

